edu.gatech.mbse.transformations.sysml2milp.utils

Class DSEMLUtils

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.gatech.mbse.transformations.sysml2milp.utils.UMLModelUtils
      • edu.gatech.mbse.transformations.sysml2milp.utils.DSEMLUtils

  • public class DSEMLUtils
extends UMLModelUtils
    Collection of functions specific to the design space exploration modeling language (DSEML).

    Interpretation and querying functions to retrieve or compute or infer elements or sets of elements from the problem definition in SysML / UML.

    Version:
    0.1
    Author:
    Sebastian

      • getAllAssociatedResourceTypes

        public static java.util.ArrayList<org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Element> getAllAssociatedResourceTypes(org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Classifier workingPrinciple)
        Get a list of resource types associated with a working principle.

        Note that this function is currently imposing some constraints on the well-formedness of the model: for each working principle, there may be at most 1 of each type of resource associated with it. Redefining properties should therefore always have a type that is a specialization of the type of the inherited redefined property.

        Parameters:
        workingPrinciple - The working principle to collect resources from
        Returns:
        A list of all resource types associated with this working principle (at any level).

      • getWorkingPrinciples

        Returns a list of all working principles associated with a particular activity.

        The function returns a set with the activity if the specified activity is a working principle itself. An empty set is returned if no working principles can be found that are associated with the particular activity specified.

        Returns:
        The list of working principles that specialize the given activity act.

      • isCompositeResource

        public static boolean isCompositeResource(org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Element e)
        Checks whether a particular resource is a composite resource.

        This function returns true or false depending on whether the specified resource is a composite resource (e.g., a robot with a gripper).

        Parameters:
        e - The resource to check.
        Returns:
